{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1cce0958-4f08-4f69-9ac3-8d184e816cb4","content":"Here's the summary:\n\n- **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` → remove it.** It was the .NET 9 opt-in flag. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` talks to MTP natively — no opt-in needed.\n- **`EnableMSTestRunner` → keep it.** This tells MSTest to build your test project as an MTP executable, which is still required.\n- **`OutputType Exe` → keep it.** Required by the MSTest runner.\n\nYour project is now correctly configured. Just run `dotnet test` as usual — it will use MTP automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9a99dcaa-7b55-448d-bb36-c73d6b8f960c","outputTokens":147,"requestId":"A039:362ABC:C4A915:E5E593:69FE872F"},"id":"f49fb938-3c3f-4840-83c9-8ecb350ae45b","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:00:37.297Z","parentId":"15fe5d61-50b8-4fb0-8d17-83591c7d71e4"}
